Sentencas: The oxygen-deficient perovskite Sr0.7Ho5.3CoO3-delta (SHCO) operates on the Co(III)/Co(II) redox couple rather than the usual Co(IV)/Co(III) couple for an oxygen reduction reaction(ORR) cathode of an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The room-temperature XRD pattern of SHCO prepared by solid-state reaction can be indexed in the tetragonal 14/mmm space group with unit-cell parameters a= 7.617 angstrom, and c= 15.293 angstrom.
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SHCO exhibits an electrical conductivity with values larger than 488 S cm(-1) over the temperature range 560-800 C. The area specific resistance (ASR) of a SHCO cathode measured on a La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O2.815 (LSGM) electrolyte reaches a relatively low value of 0.14 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With a 300-mu m-thick LSGM disk as the electrolyte and NiO-GDC as the anode, a cell with the SHCO cathode exhibited maximum power densities of 1274, 756, and 493 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800, and 750 degrees C, respectively, with hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cross-section scanning-electron-microscopy measurements confirmed the porous microstructure of the electrodes and good electrode-buffer layer-electrolyte adherence in a single test cell.
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ORR activity of a SHCO cathode operating on the Co(III)/Co(II) couple approaches that of the best cathodes operating on the Co(IV)/Co(III) couple, and higher-spin Co(III) ions provide a compatible thermal expansion.
Titulo: Sr0.7Ho0.3CoO3-δ as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
